{
  "texts": [
    "This approach enables the models to capture the importance of different words or elements to attend to, resulting in significant performance improvements and providing interpretable results.",
    "CNNs and RNNs primarily focus on a limited scope of word-level information, making it challenging to capture long-distance dependencies and learn deep semantics.",
    "In contrast, recent studies proposed the utilization of pre-trained models, such as BERT, to represent the contextual information of essays with rich semantic understanding.",
    "Pre-trained models are deep learning models trained on extensive datasets and can be used as-is or fine-tuned for specific tasks.",
    "BERT (Devlin et al. 2018), which stands for Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers, is a pre-trained bidirectional encoder-only transformer."
  ]
}